Located between Lausanne and Geneva, Morges was founded
in 1286 by the Dukes of Savoy, on the shores of Lake
Geneva. With its castle and its port, it has been a
regional economic and political center for a long time.
The city is sourrounded by the biggest wine-making
region of the Lake Geneva area. On your tour through
the historic city center, you can visit a lot of
different wine cellars and taste the local production.
Continue your tour and check out the castle of Morges
with its museums, the beautiful seaside and historic
port. Don't miss the old Protestant church of Morges
with its magnificient belltower, built in 1306.
